        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-07-19T11:50:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-07-19T11:50:00-05:00" n="250"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                <head>250. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Brazil</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d250fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 732.5/7–1958. Secret. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_SEV1"
                            >Siracusa</persName> and approved and signed by <persName
                            corresp="#p_BMM1">Bernbaum</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-07-19T12:50:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1958—12:50 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>103. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 101.<note n="2" xml:id="d250fn2"
                        >Telegram 101, July 18, informed the Embassy in Brazil that the military aid
                        program was presented to the Brazilians by U.S. military representatives at
                        the Joint Brazil-United States Defense Commission meeting on July 18. (<hi
                            rend="italic">ibid</hi>., 732.5/7–1858) The estimated value of the
                        equipment offered was $87.1 million. A copy of the minutes of the meeting is
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>., <gloss target="#t_ARA1">ARA</gloss>/<gloss
                            target="#t_EST1">EST</gloss> Files: Lot 62 D 308, Talks Under Article
                        VI.</note> Minister <persName corresp="#p_VHR1">Valle</persName> said last
                    night Air Force and Navy apparently content, especially Air Force, but believed
                    Army very disappointed its share program. Dept officers replied program devised
                    basis military criteria justifiable under U.S. programs. Since <gloss
                        target="#t_ASW1">ASW</gloss> most significant role hemisphere defense
                    logical Navy and Air shares stressed. Suggested this posed problem for Brazil
                    not U.S. and that our programs should permit readjustment Brazil’s own military
                    budgeting in order further beef up Army if that considered necessary. <persName
                        corresp="#p_VHR1">Valle</persName> emphasized political dominance Army over
                    other Services and greater importance its internal security role against
                    communism.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
